title: Love Island Australia's Cassie Lansdell starred on Made in Chelsea
text:
Cassie Lansdell is already making waves in the Love Island Australia villa.

But it seems the London-born beauty is no stranger to being in front of the cameras.

The 26-year-old, who moved to Australia six years ago, revealed to WHO magazine that she previously starred in the UK reality show Made in Chelsea.

So THAT'S where we've seen her before! Love Island Australia's Cassie Lansdell (left) has revealed she previously starred on UK reality show Made in Chelsea. Pictured with Francis Boulle (centre) and a female friend (right)

Cassie said she was an 'extra' on the long-running E4 show, which documents the lives of London's young and wealthy elite.

Back in 2012, the executive assistant shared several photos of herself posing with Made in Chelsea cast members.

She was pictured with the likes of Andy Jordan and Francis Boulle.

Cheers to fame! Back in 2012, the executive assistant shared several photos of herself posing with Made in Chelsea cast members, including Andy Jordan (centre)

Looking for love: London-born Cassie (pictured) is no stranger to being in front of the cameras

Meanwhile, Cassie also told WHO that she was worried she wouldn't be accepted on the show because she wasn't born in Australia.

'I was thinking, "They're definitely not going to want me on there because I'm not Australian",' she said.

Born and raised in London, Cassie comes from a mixed Chinese-English background.

She has had three Australian boyfriends but has been single for the past eight months after her most recent ex left her heartbroken.

Cassie is currently coupled up with the villa's resident 'bad boy' Adam Farrugia, but their partnership is already on the rocks.

Viewers flocked to defend her during Monday night's episode when a thoughtless comment from Adam left her in tears.

He had dismissively said Cassie 'wasn't a bad looking girl', leaving her humiliated.
description: Cassie Lansdell is already making waves in the Love Island Australia villa.
authors: Jess Bell For Daily Mail Australia
